com.sonyericsson.extras.liveware.extension.util.sensor

クラス AccessorySensor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sonyericsson.extras.liveware.extension.util.sensor.AccessorySensor

  • public class AccessorySensor
extends java.lang.Object
    The accessory sensor class is used to interact with a sensor on an accessory.

    • コンストラクタの詳細

      • AccessorySensor

        public AccessorySensor(Context context,
               java.lang.String hostAppPackageName,
               int sensorId,
               AccessorySensorType type,
               boolean isInterruptSupported,
               java.lang.String name,
               int resolution,
               int minimumDelay,
               int maximumRange)
        Create accessory sensor. This constructor is normally not called directly. Instead it is created from AccessorySensorManager or DeviceInfo.
        パラメータ:
        context - The context.
        hostAppPackageName - The host application package name.
        sensorId - The sensor id.
        type - The sensor type.
        isInterruptSupported - True if interrupt mode is supported.
        name - The name.
        resolution - The resolution.
        minimumDelay - The minimum delay.
        maximumRange - The maximum range.

                    int sensorRate,
                    int interruptMode)
                      throws AccessorySensorException
        Register a sensor event listener. It is only possible to have one listener per sensor.

        sensorRate - The sensor rate.
        interruptMode - The interrupt mode.
